<subSubSection pageId="126" pageNumber="523" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="126.[1398,2611,292,1156]" pageId="126" pageNumber="523">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1404,1755,882,915]" pageId="126" pageNumber="523">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. Although Jouvenet’s White-toothed Shrew has a relatively small and scattered distribution, is considered very common where it is found, and makes up 10-25% of shrews captured throughout various regions.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
